{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\nThe rollout must guarantee that enabling `identity.require_authenticated` breaks nothing on\nthe Gerrit side. But not every Gerrit-side service writes **in-scope** ticket events, so the\nstory is to classify them correctly, not to blanket-sign everything:\n\n- The **opcert-service never pushes to the store** — `src/rebar/opcert_service/jobs.py`: \"The\n  server never pushes. The whole job runs with `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off`.\" It produces op-certs in\n  an ephemeral, remote-stripped workspace; it writes no in-scope authorship events.\n- The **review-bot writes `code_review` tickets, which are gate-EXEMPT** —\n  `src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py:125`:\n  `_GATE_EXEMPT_TYPES = (\"session_log\", \"code_review\", \"identity\")`.\n\nSo the real target is any Gerrit-side operation that writes **non-exempt work tickets**\n(a reconciler / inbound translation), which must be signed.\n\n## What\n\n- Enumerate every Gerrit-side operation that touches the ticket store and classify each as\n  **non-writing** (opcert-service, `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off`), **gate-exempt** (review-bot\n  `code_review`), or **in-scope writer** (a Gerrit-side reconciler / inbound translation that\n  writes work tickets).\n- For each in-scope writer, confirm it has a materialized `0600` signing key + a `git\n  user.email` matching its identity and produces a **signed** event.\n- Finish canary 1787's deferred post-deploy validation for the in-scope path.\n\n## Scope\n\nGerrit-side operations only. Classification + verification; provisioning only where an\nin-scope writer is found unsigned. No enforcement flip here.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Every Gerrit-side store operation is enumerated and classified non-writing /\n      gate-exempt / in-scope-writer, with file/line evidence for the non-writing and exempt\n      classifications.\n- [ ] Each **in-scope** Gerrit-side writer produces a **signed** event under a materialized\n      `0600` key; `rebar verify-identity` reports it `verified`.\n- [ ] Confirmed unaffected by enforcement: the opcert-service (`REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off`, never\n      pushes) and the review-bot (`code_review`, gate-exempt) are not rejected when\n      `require_authenticated=true`.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] the canary is re-run on the deployed VM for the in-scope path; the\n      signed event id / log (or a documented \"no in-scope Gerrit-side writer exists\") is\n      recorded on this ticket."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784228116251491001,"uuid":"cdb1700c-1819-4024-a303-ece06e0961c0"}